---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import AffiliateCTA from '../../components/AffiliateCTA.astro';
import { AFFILIATE_LINKS as affiliates } from '../../config/affiliate-links';

const title = 'AI Website Builder Domain Setup Guide (2025)';
const description = 'How to set up your custom domain with any AI website builder. Step-by-step instructions for all major platforms.';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="mb-12">
      <p class="text-orange-600 font-semibold mb-4">GUIDE</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">AI Website Builder Domain Setup Guide</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-6">
        How to connect your custom domain to any AI website builder.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-orange-50 border-l-4 border-orange-500 p-6 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Quick Answer</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg">
        <strong>Buy your domain first</strong> (Namecheap, Google Domains, or your builder). Then connect it in your builder settings.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700">
        <strong>Cost:</strong> $10-15/year for a domain. Always worth it for professionalism.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Step 1: Buy Your Domain</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
          <strong>Where to buy:</strong>
        </p>

        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 ml-4 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Namecheap:</strong> Reliable, good prices, solid management interface</li>
          <li><strong>Google Domains:</strong> Clean interface, includes privacy protection</li>
          <li><strong>Builder's domain service:</strong> Convenient but often more expensive</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-gray-700 mt-4">
          <strong>Recommendation:</strong> Buy from Namecheap or Google Domains. Easier to manage if you switch builders later.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-6 mt-6">
          <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold">
            <strong>Tip:</strong> Buy a .com if available. It's still the most trusted extension. If not, .co or your country extension works.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Step 2: Connect Domain to Your Builder</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Method A: Point Nameservers (Recommended)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            <strong>Best for:</strong> Most users, easier management
          </p>
          <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-gray-700 ml-4 space-y-2">
            <li>Go to your domain registrar (where you bought the domain)</li>
            <li>Find DNS settings or nameservers</li>
            <li>Replace existing nameservers with your builder's nameservers</li>
            <li>Wait 2-48 hours for propagation</li>
          </ol>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Method B: DNS Records</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            <strong>Best for:</strong> Advanced users, keeping email separate
          </p>
          <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-gray-700 ml-4 space-y-2">
            <li>Get A record or CNAME from your builder</li>
            <li>Add DNS record at your domain registrar</li>
            <li>Wait 2-48 hours for propagation</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Platform-Specific Instructions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">10Web</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Settings → Custom Domain → Add domain. Choose nameservers or DNS method. Follow their specific instructions in the dashboard.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Framer</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Site Settings → Domains → Connect Custom Domain. Framer provides clear instructions for each registrar.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Durable</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Settings → Domain. Simple process, usually takes less than 5 minutes to set up.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Squarespace</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Settings → Domains → Use a Domain I Own. Squarespace has excellent step-by-step guides.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Wix</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Settings → Domains → Connect your domain. Wix offers both nameserver and DNS connection methods.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">SSL Certificate (HTTPS)</h2>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border-l-4 border-green-500 p-6 mb-8">
        <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold">
          <strong>Good news:</strong> All modern AI website builders include SSL certificates automatically. Your site will have HTTPS by default.
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="text-gray-700">
        SSL encrypts data between your site and visitors. Google penalizes non-HTTPS sites. All builders mentioned here include SSL free.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Troubleshooting</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Domain Not Working After 48 Hours</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Check that nameservers or DNS records are entered correctly. Even small typos break things. Contact support if stuck.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">WWW Works But Non-WWW Does not (or vice versa)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Set up redirect in builder settings. Redirect one to the other (usually non-WWW to WWW or vice versa).
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Email Not Working</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            If using builder's email, check MX records. If using external email (Google Workspace), DNS records must point correctly.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Timeline</h2>

      <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2">
        <li>Buy domain: 5-10 minutes</li>
        <li>Connect to builder: 10-30 minutes</li>
        <li>Propagation: 2-48 hours (usually faster, like 2-6 hours)</li>
        <li><strong>Total: Same day to working site</strong></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="text-center">
      <AffiliateCTA
        href={affiliates['10web'].affiliateUrl}
        commission={affiliates['10web'].commission}
        label="Start Building (Add Domain Later)"
        className="bg-orange-600 hover:bg-orange-700 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-semibold text-lg inline-block"
      />
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
